        <h1>Instructions</h1>
        <p class="lead pr-5">
        <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
            <li class="list-group-item border-0">Each person has to register individually – on the Samgatha site.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item border-0">On completion of registration, an acknowledgement mail will be sent to your email id.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item border-0">It is compulsory to bring your college ID card and the payment acknowledgement mail when you enter the campus.</li>
        </ul>
        
<p>
**Faculty members should also register on the site and all the rules apply to them too.
**Please note that a limited number of seats are available which will be filled based on first-come, first-serve basis. </p>
    <h1>On reaching the campus</h1>
        <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
            <li class="list-group-item border-0">Students will have to make an entry on the register near the main gate.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item border-0">Female participants are requested to reach the campus before 10:00 pm on the day of arrival.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item border-0">Following this, participants who require accommodation must register at the adjacent Hospitality Desk by producing a soft-copy/printout of the acknowledgement mail sent to them.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item border-0">The participants must check out at the hospitality desk/main gate to acknowledge that they’ve left the institute.</li>
        </ul>
        <h1>How to reach?</h1>
        <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
            <li>IIITDM Kancheepuram is located in Kandigai, in Vandalur-Kelambakkam road, 18 kms from Tambaram.</li>
            <li>The best way to reach is by bus.</li>
            <li>55D takes you directly to IIITDM’s doorsteps. </li>
            <li>For other buses, Tambaram -> Kandigai (bus) -> IIITDMK (Auto at Kandigai bus stop).</li>
            <li>Buses are also available from Vandalur gate/zoo, which brings you straight to Kandigai.</li>
        </ul>
        <h1>Rules of stay</h1>
        <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
            <li class="list-group-item border-0">Smoking, drinking and other drug consumptions are strictly prohibited and necessary action will be taken by the institute if a participant is found to be in possession of these items.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item border-0">Any damage to institution facilities and property provided to the participants would result in serious action and necessary reimbursement charges would have to be dealt by the participants who are found guilty.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item border-0">Participants are expected to not create any kind of nuisance which might trouble other participants in the room.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item border-0">The college will not be responsible for any damage or loss of property or valuables stored in places of accommodation.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item border-0">Upon check-out, the Guest should settle all the accounts with regard to the services rendered and return the receipt to the organisers. </li>
            <li class="list-group-item border-0">The decision of organisers is final and binding in case of any dispute.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item border-0">Fare : Rs.150 per day(Non AC Accomodation)<li>
        </ul>
        <h1>FAQ</h1>
        
        <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
<li class="list-group-item border-0">Do the accommodation charges include food?</li>
<p class="lead pr-5">No, but you can make use of the canteens/food stalls available during Samgatha at your own expense.</p>

<li class="list-group-item border-0">Can I register for accommodation after I arrive at IIITDM?</li>
<p class="lead pr-5">Yes, the hospitality desk operates all the time and you can register with them anytime you want.</p>
PS: Full accommodation charges will have to be paid.

<li class="list-group-item border-0">Do I need different passports for the Pro-shows?</li>
<p class="lead pr-5">No, the Samgatha passport covers for all your events occurring in IIITDM, except for informal and fun side events.</p>

<li class="list-group-item border-0">Does IIIT have a curfew for in-time and out-time?<li>
<p class="lead pr-5">Yes, students will be allowed to enter/exit at the main gate only at 06:00 – 22:30 hours.</p>

<li class="list-group-item border-0">What are the documents I’m supposed to bring?</li>
<p class="lead pr-5">Just the Samgatha passport and your institute ID card for verification.</p>

</ol>
